Iavan Pijoos, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Somerset West - A municipal worker was killed and three were injured when a refuse truck overturned in Somerset West, Western Cape, on Friday afternoon, paramedics said. The 20-year-old man was found a few metres from the truck, which was on its side in the middle of the road, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said. The driver apparently lost control of the vehicle and it overturned. The three injured men were treated on the scene and transported to Mediclinic Vergelegen. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.